        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-03T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-03T03:00:00-05:00" n="877" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d877">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stuart, J. Leighton: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-03T16:00:00+08:00">May 3, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 3—8:04 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>924. For first time today Ambassador permitted by guards at this compound to
                    visit Chancery. Embassy personnel also travelled about with little interference,
                    some in cars. A few were challenged on street but permitted proceed upon
                    identification.</p>
                <p>Repeated OffEmb Canton 344, Shanghai 419.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
